# 3. 崩れていく仮面

Mizuki: <It's been twenty minutes since lunch began... I guess Yuki isn't coming today either...>
Kanade: <...>
Ena: <Wait, someone just logged in. Is that...?>
Mafuyu's Message: <Are you all still here?>
Mizuki: <Yuki! You came...!>
Ena: <Is everything okay? You said you had to take a break from N25...>
Mafuyu's Message: <I can't stay long... I'm just here to take a quick break.>
Kanade: <Okay, but I'm glad you're here...>
Mizuki: <Then, the rest of us should get to work! Our new song's actually almost finished!>
Mizuki: <I made this effect based on your lyrics, Yuki, and want to see what you think!>
Ena: <Oh, me too. Can you see if my rough sketch captures what you were going for with your lyrics?>
Mafuyu's Message: <Okay.>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (Now that I'm hearing them together, these lyrics don't really work with this melody. Maybe I should go with something more straightforward...)
Mafuyu: (Yes, this should be better...)
Mafuyu: (Kanade's songs always feel so warm...)
Mafuyu: (Also...)
Mizuki: <Oh, Enanan! I need you to do a tiny favor for me!>
Ena: <You're not talking about adding an extra section again, are you?>
Mizuki: <I am! I've got a feeling that the part during the chorus is gonna look even better if we added a cut where she extends her hand out!>
Ena: <Extend her hand out...? With the current composition, that means I'm gonna have to draw all of that in.>
Mizuki: <I know but it'll make Yuki's lyrics hit just that much harder!>
Ena: <Hmm... Yeah, I get what you mean...>
Kanade: <I agree. I like this idea.>
Ena: <Wait, K, you do? Then, I'll give it a try...>
Mizuki: <Hey, talk about Miss Double Standards...>
Mafuyu: (Their usual banter...)
Mafuyu: (Just hearing their voices helps put my mind at ease...)
Miku: <I'm glad you did this, Mafuyu...>
Mafuyu: Huh?
Miku: <You seem to be feeling a little better now.>
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: Yes, you may be right...
Mafuyu's Message: <I'm finished fixing my lyrics.>
Kanade: <You are? Thank you, Yuki.>
Mizuki: <Interesting... I think I'll need to adjust how to show it on screen a little.>
Mizuki: <Once Enanan's done making that hand asset we talked about, I'll try putting a cut together based on these lyrics!>
Ena: <About that hand... You know I pretty much have to draw it again from scratch, right?>
Mizuki: <Which is why you're the best! Thanks for doing this, Enanan♪>
Kanade: <Hehe...>
Mizuki: <So, now that the lyrics are done, I should be able to finish all my touch-ups today if I really try. We could conceivably be finished by tomorrow.>
Kanade: <Yes, if we record the vocals today and edit everything tomorrow, I'd say it'll be ready for upload by that evening.>
Ena: <Then, tomorrow's all about cleaning it up. I'm almost done too, so I'll try doing what I can again tomorrow.>
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu's Message: <I don't know if I'll be here tomorrow.>
Mizuki: <Oh, right... You still need to study.>
Mizuki: <Still, don't you want to finish what we've been working on together...?>
Mafuyu: Oh...
Ena: <Yeah, Mizuki has a point.>
Ena: <We'll let you know when we're about to upload it, so try to be there for that. I mean, it was a group effort...>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu's Message: <Then, I'll see what I can do...>
Mafuyu's Message: <And I'll let you all know if I can't make it.>
Mizuki: <...! Thanks, Yuki!>
Ena: <We'll be waiting for you.>
Teacher: Thank you for coming all this way. So, shall we get started?
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, let's.
Mafuyu's Mother: Still, I feel terrible about asking you to meet with me so suddenly. I know parent-teacher conferences don't take place for some time.
Mafuyu's Mother: But my daughter's been behaving so oddly at home lately. It's really quite worrisome...
Mafuyu's Mother: Which is why I was hoping to hear how she's been at school.
Teacher: Ah, I see. It's normal for a parent to be concerned about their child, so I understand.
Mafuyu's Mother: Thank you very much. So...
Mafuyu's Mother: How has Mafuyu been lately?
Teacher: Normal as far as I can tell... She's been fulfilling her responsibilities as a class representative as always, and is adored by all her peers. I couldn't ask for a better student.
Mafuyu's Mother: I see...
Mafuyu's Mother: Was there anything else? I would appreciate anything you could share with me, even if it's minor...
Teacher: Hmm... Well...
Teacher: Actually... She did make quite a few mistakes on her finals. It was strange to see...
Mafuyu's Mother: What...?
Teacher: To be fair, we all have our bad days, so I'm sure it's no cause for concern.
Teacher: It's just... She hardly ever makes careless mistakes like that, so–
Mafuyu's Mother: Excuse me. What are you talking about...?
Mafuyu's Mother: You've already finished grading her finals?
Teacher: Huh? Yes, I handed them back the other day... I assumed she'd already told you.
Mafuyu's Mother: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: Hello? Yes, this is Mafuyu Asahina's mother.
Mafuyu's Mother: I apologize for calling you so suddenly.
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, that's right... How has Mafuyu been acting lately?
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes... I see...
Mafuyu's Mother: She didn't show up today...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, I agree. She's always working very hard, so I'll remind her that she needs to take breaks on occasion...
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay. Thank you very much...
Mafuyu's Mother: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: (What's gotten into her...?)
Mafuyu's Mother: (She hid how she did on her finals from me and didn't show up for cram school...)
Mafuyu's Mother: This can only mean...
Mafuyu's Mother: (If this keeps up, she's going to lose focus and not do as well as she needs to on her entrance exams...)
Mafuyu's Mother: (Which means she won't get accepted to her top choice.)
Mafuyu's Mother: That is simply not an option...
